snippet.description:
Click here to Subscribe to SAB TV Channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/sabtv?sub_confirmation=1

Click to watch all the episodes of Taarak Mehta Ka Ooltah Chashmah https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL6Rtnh6YJK7Zfu1x9Bd1UqLwUxhZ1oBJh

The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in """"Gokuldham Co-operative Society"""" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - Promoolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalaal.

snippet.title: Mere Yaar - N-Gritz Feat. Sarang Sikander | YJKD Season 2 - 30th Sept | Latest Punjabi Song 2020
snippet.description:
Exactly two Years ago, Troll Punjabi Came out with Punjab's First web series "Yaar Jigree Kasooti Degree". And, after huge sucess of the first season, we are all set to bring you the first Promotional song "Mere Yaar" from Free Fire presents "Yaar Jigri Kasuti Degree Season 2". First Episode of the much-awaited new season is all set to premiere on 30th September on Troll Punjabi.

Season 1 of Yaar Jigri Kasooti Degree ended in total chaos. Events unfolded in such a way that our beloved characters were set on different paths and were separated from each other. Jass and Ekam were left alone and without a roof. Lucky's actions ended him in jail and where he awaits his fate. Heartbroken Roop felt guilty for what he has done to people close to him. Uncertain of his future, Anmol has to give up all his dreams and returned home. 


Written & Directed by Rabby Tiwana
Starring : Pukhraj Bhalla, Prateek Singh Rai, Sukhdeep Sapra, Karan Sandhawalia, Karanvir Deol 
Singer: N-Gritz Feat Sarang Sikander 
(Insta : sarangsikander786) 
Music: JT Beats (Insta : beatsbybhatti)

Colourist: Prince K Makkar

Co-Actors: Sukhi Patran, Babar Khan, Chamkour Billa, Dilveer Dill, Satnam Dhuri

Recreated from

Song Lyrics -
Yaad aunde ne oh saal,vakhri sigi chaal,
College de c o din katte c yaaran naal,
kiven c ande jaande,kiven kudi ptaunde,
kiven gandasse chak vairiyan naa(naal) vair nbhaunde

bhul diyan ni raatan naal btayiyan jedi,
sukh ya dukh hove sige hamesha ready,
rabba tu das ve tu kalla kyun chadeya,
sinne cho dil kad tainu ki ae milya??????????

bhul ni pavanga mai oh saare lamhe,
dukh ne jede aj karde tang ne,
akha vich athru ni oh sarre bharge,
jede c naal aj dur kithe chalge,

hundi ni baardaash mere to ne hun duriyan,
zindgi boj ban gayi ae majbooriyan
likh ke geet aj zindagi mai khojda
kiven kar javan os pal ch mai sochda..

Ik-ik gal jediiiiii yaaran naal kitti aj baike mai oh gal sochdan
Ik-ik khushi jediiii ohne ne ditti band kamre baike aj khojdan
Rabba das de kithe ne o saare mere yaar X2

Tusi ta sige jine pehlan c plai mainu,
Tusi c jine pehli kudi c ptai mainu,
Tusi c jinne pehlan stage te chadaya mainu
Tusi ta sige jitho dillo pyaar aya mainu

Jdo c lod mainu sare marij c,
yaar hi c mere jinaaa likhi taqdeer c,
rabba maaf kari naaaa bura tu man ji,
mai tainu bhul ju par yaari ni bhul ni,

maafi mangda, jinna to naio mang paya,
aj labdaa ohnanuuu jinne jinna sakhaya,
yaarian na rabba kade kisse di dur kari,
jede vichde c aj ona da v mel kari,

yarri nu salaam jinne saath nabhaya,
naal mere khad es makaaam te punchaya,
ik ik kar hun jana mai ohna kol,
jina ne bnayi meri zindagi anmol..

Ik-2 gal jediiiiii ... X2

Chal paya mai os raah jithe yaar mere 
Labh ni paa reha mai jhere riste c gehre
Socha vich pya mai kive dikhava mukh
Hor vi ni chara jitho mainu miluga sukh
Hun na tu roki rabba ehi ardaas meri
Jann layi tu himmat davi aahi umeed meri
Raah vich je digeya ta tuhi sambhal li
Par kise na kise tu othe pohncha di 
Jithe rehnde yaar mere dilo dildaar mere
Akhan de sukh ne oh ohi ne pyaar mere
Akhan ne bhariya ne hun rabb gawah ehda
Athru mithaun yaar aahi khwaab mera
Poora bharosa nale yakeen v
Yaar jad milu hou dastan haseen g
Jaan ge russ oh galat v kehn ge
Par maaf kar mainu gal naal v rehn 
Ik-2 gal jediiiiii ..... X2

snippet.title: What About Thoughts? | Day 14  of the 21 Day Meditation Challenge with Gurudev
snippet.description:
Trying to still the mind through any kind of effort is like catching air in your fist. By knowing the nature of the mind, you realise the key to finding a space of stillness.

Maximize happiness, health & immunity. Cut down stress, anxiety, and depression! Learn the powerful breathing technique Sudarshan Kriya, along with Pranayama, Yoga, Meditation and Practical Tips for everyday living in the online Meditation and Breath workshop (The Art of Living Happiness Program).

 Register now üëâüèΩ https://aolf.in/ytonlinehp

#21DayMeditationChallenge 

About Gurudev Sri Sri Ravi Shankar

Gurudev Sri Sri Ravi Shankar is a world-renowned humanitarian, spiritual leader, and an ambassador of peace and human values. Through his life and work, Gurudev has inspired millions around the world with a vision of a stress-free and violence-free world.
Gurudev founded The Art of Living, a non-profit organization that is engaged in stress-management and service initiatives. The programs designed by Gurudev empower people with techniques and tools to live a deeper and blissful life.

#Gurudev #SriSriRaviShankar

The show is inspired from the famous humorous column 'Duniya Ne Undha Chasma' written by the eminent Gujarati writer Mr. Tarak Mehta. This story evolves around happenings in """"Gokuldham Co-operative Society"""" and covers topical issues which are socially relevant. The show predominantly - Promoolves around 'Jethalaal' (Dilip Joshi) who is an uneducated Gujarati businessman. Your 'Taarak Mehta' (Sailesh Lodha), is his neighbor. 'Jethalaal' finds a friend and philosopher in 'Taarak Mehta' and often goes to him for advice whenever he is in trouble. Jethalaal's family includes his simpleton wife 'Daya Ben' (Disha Wakani) and a mischievous son 'Tapu' (Bhavya Gandhi). Tapu is a menace and a constant source of trouble to all the members of Gokuldham. They have often warned 'Jethalaal' to reform 'Tapu' or else be prepared to leave the premises. Lost hopes of being heard by his son push Jethalaal' to call his father 'Champaklal' (Amit Bhatt) from the village. This was his great idea of leashing some control over the mischievous Tapu. The opposite happens and the grandfather joins hands with the grandson to make life a roller coaster troublesome ride for Jethalaal.

snippet.title: Star Wars: Squadrons ‚Äì ‚ÄúHunted‚Äù CG Short
snippet.description:
The New Republic fleet strikes the Imperial dockyard at Var-Shaa. Pre-order STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons now to get cosmetic items featured in this short film: https://www.ea.com/games/starwars/squadrons/cg-short-hunted 

The Empire‚Äôs retreat after a surprise attack marks yet another stumble in the wake of the second Death Star‚Äôs destruction. But for one member of Titan Squadron, the battle is far from over. Squadron Leader Varko Grey finds himself as the last TIE pilot on the battlefield, hunted relentlessly by a renegade New Republic X-wing in this standalone STAR WARS: Squadrons story.

Made in collaboration by Motive Studios, Lucasfilm, and ILM, "Hunted" is set before the events of STAR WARS: Squadrons, introducing you to one of the ace pilots who you'll be fighting alongside in the story to unfold.

Master the art of starfighter combat in the authentic piloting experience STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons, available October 2, 2020 on PlayStation¬Æ4, Xbox One, PC on EA.com, Steam, and Epic Games Store, and playable in Virtual Reality (VR) on PlayStation 4 and PC with cross-play support.

Pre-order to get the Var-Shaa Hunter and Var-Shaa Survivor cosmetic items, inspired by the short film: https://www.ea.com/games/starwars/squadrons/buy

Follow EA Star Wars:
https://twitter.com/EAStarWars
https://www.instagram.com/eastarwars/
https://www.facebook.com/EAStarWars/

About STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons:

ALL WINGS REPORT IN ‚Äì Plan skirmishes with your squadron in the briefing room before taking off to the evolving battlefields across the galaxy. Compete in intense 5v5 multiplayer dogfights or unite with your squadron to tip the scales in monumental fleet battles. Together, you‚Äôre the galaxy‚Äôs finest.

MASTER LEGENDARY STARFIGHTERS ‚Äì Take control of different classes of starfighters from both the New Republic and Imperial fleets ‚Äì including the agile A-wing and the devastating TIE bomber. Modify your ship, divert the power between its systems, and destroy your opponents in strategic space dogfights.

GET IN THE COCKPIT ‚Äì The cockpit is your home. Use its dashboards to your advantage and ‚Äì with just a thin hull of metal and glass between you and the perils of space ‚Äì feel the intensity of combat from a first-person perspective. Take off in thrilling multiplayer modes and a unique single-player STAR WARS‚Ñ¢ story, which covers a key campaign near the conclusion of the Galactic Civil War. Immerse yourself in the pilot‚Äôs seat completely with the option to play the entirety of STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons in Virtual Reality (VR) on PSVR and PC.

THE MISSION IS CLEAR ‚Äì STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons is a fully self-contained experience from day one, where you earn rewards through play. Climb the ranks and unlock new components like weapons, hulls, engines, shields, and cosmetic items in a clear path for progression that keeps gameplay fresh and engaging.

snippet.title: Did We Just Detect Life on Venus?
snippet.description:
The announcement of the detection of a possible biomarker in the atmosphere of Venus has shook up the field of astrobiology and grabbed headlines across the world. Today, we explore why Venus could plausibly host life, how this detection was made, and whether it really means that we've finally found extraterrestrial life. Written and presented by Prof Kipping, featuring guest Dr Caleb Scharf.

You can now support our research program and the Cool Worlds Lab at Columbia University: https://www.coolworldslab.com/support

Thank-you to Kevin Clark, Tom Widdowson, Denny Smith, Stephanie Hackley, Mark Sloan, Laura Sanborn, Kolos Kantor, Patrick Herman, Abel Aganbegyan, Claudio Bottaccini, Daniel Brunk, Douglas Daughaday, Scott Fincher, James Kindred, Andrew Jones, Jason Allen, Steven Baldwin, Jason Black, Stuart Brownlee, Shivam Chaturvedi, David Denholm, Tim Dorais, Glen Downton, Eneko Urrestarazu, Gordon Fulton, Sean Griffiths, Peter Halloran, John Jurcevic, Niklas Kildal, Jack Kobernick, Wes Kobernick, Valeri Kremer, Marc Lijoi, Sheri Loftin, Branden Loizides, Anatoliy Maslyanchuk, Blair Matson, Ocean Mcintyre, Laini Mitchell, Jeffrey Needle, Andr√© Pelletier, Juan Rivillas, Bret Robinson, Zenith Star, Lauren Steely, Ernest Stefan-Matyus, Mark Steven, Elena West, Barrett York, Tristan Zajonc, Preetumsingh Gowd, Shaun Kelsey, Chuck Wolfred, David Vennel, Emre Dessoi, Fahid Naeem, Francisco Rebolledo, Hauke Laging, James Falls, Jon Adams, Michael Gremillion, Pierce Rutherford, Trev Kline, Tristan Leger, Lasse Skov & Takashi Hanai.

::Paper announcing the detection::
‚ñ∫ Greaves, J. et al. (2020), "Phosphine gas in the cloud decks of Venus", Nature Astronomy: https://doi.org/10.1038/s41550-020-1174-4

::Other references used::
‚ñ∫ Sousa-Silva. C. et al. (2019), "Phosphine as a Biosignature Gas in Exoplanet Atmosphere", 
Astrobiology, 20, 235: https://arxiv.org/abs/1910.05224
‚ñ∫ Way, M. et al. (2016), "Was Venus the First Habitable World of our Solar System?", Geophysical Research Letters, 43, 8376: https://arxiv.org/abs/1608.00706
‚ñ∫ Moses, J. et al. (2005), "Photochemistry and diffusion in Jupiter's stratosphere: Constraints from ISO observations and comparisons with other giant planets", J. Geophys. Res., 110, E08001: https://doi.org/doi:10.1029/2005JE002411

::Movies/TV scenes used::
‚ñ∫ Roving Mars (2006) Buena Vista Pictures
‚ñ∫ Exploring Venus (2019) Magellan TV
‚ñ∫ Star Trek (1966) Paramount Pictures

::Other video footage used::
‚ñ∫ ALMA timelapse by ESO/Jos√© Francisco Salgado: https://youtu.be/Tn8Udphi6JA
‚ñ∫ Venus UV footage by Akatsuki/JAXA: https://www.isas.jaxa.jp/en/topics/002099.html
‚ñ∫ Bill Clinton footage form the Presidential Library & White House Television
‚ñ∫ Galaxies fly through by SDSS/Miguel Aragon/Mark Subbarao/Alex Szalay: https://youtu.be/08LBltePDZw

snippet.localized.title: Did We Just Detect Life on Venus?
snippet.localized.description:
The announcement of the detection of a possible biomarker in the atmosphere of Venus has shook up the field of astrobiology and grabbed headlines across the world. Today, we explore why Venus could plausibly host life, how this detection was made, and whether it really means that we've finally found extraterrestrial life. Written and presented by Prof Kipping, featuring guest Dr Caleb Scharf.

You can now support our research program and the Cool Worlds Lab at Columbia University: https://www.coolworldslab.com/support

Thank-you to Kevin Clark, Tom Widdowson, Denny Smith, Stephanie Hackley, Mark Sloan, Laura Sanborn, Kolos Kantor, Patrick Herman, Abel Aganbegyan, Claudio Bottaccini, Daniel Brunk, Douglas Daughaday, Scott Fincher, James Kindred, Andrew Jones, Jason Allen, Steven Baldwin, Jason Black, Stuart Brownlee, Shivam Chaturvedi, David Denholm, Tim Dorais, Glen Downton, Eneko Urrestarazu, Gordon Fulton, Sean Griffiths, Peter Halloran, John Jurcevic, Niklas Kildal, Jack Kobernick, Wes Kobernick, Valeri Kremer, Marc Lijoi, Sheri Loftin, Branden Loizides, Anatoliy Maslyanchuk, Blair Matson, Ocean Mcintyre, Laini Mitchell, Jeffrey Needle, Andr√© Pelletier, Juan Rivillas, Bret Robinson, Zenith Star, Lauren Steely, Ernest Stefan-Matyus, Mark Steven, Elena West, Barrett York, Tristan Zajonc, Preetumsingh Gowd, Shaun Kelsey, Chuck Wolfred, David Vennel, Emre Dessoi, Fahid Naeem, Francisco Rebolledo, Hauke Laging, James Falls, Jon Adams, Michael Gremillion, Pierce Rutherford, Trev Kline, Tristan Leger, Lasse Skov & Takashi Hanai.

::Paper announcing the detection::
‚ñ∫ Greaves, J. et al. (2020), "Phosphine gas in the cloud decks of Venus", Nature Astronomy: https://doi.org/10.1038/s41550-020-1174-4

::Other references used::
‚ñ∫ Sousa-Silva. C. et al. (2019), "Phosphine as a Biosignature Gas in Exoplanet Atmosphere", 
Astrobiology, 20, 235: https://arxiv.org/abs/1910.05224
‚ñ∫ Way, M. et al. (2016), "Was Venus the First Habitable World of our Solar System?", Geophysical Research Letters, 43, 8376: https://arxiv.org/abs/1608.00706
‚ñ∫ Moses, J. et al. (2005), "Photochemistry and diffusion in Jupiter's stratosphere: Constraints from ISO observations and comparisons with other giant planets", J. Geophys. Res., 110, E08001: https://doi.org/doi:10.1029/2005JE002411

::Movies/TV scenes used::

snippet.title: Would You Swim In Power Plant Wastewater?
snippet.description:
Normally, the answer would be no. But in these very limited circumstances, at Iceland's Blue Lagoon, you can swim in geothermal power plant wastewater, and it's even healthy: although the marketing material doesn't usually mention it. Here's a story about geothermal energy, cheap heat, and how to keep some ducks warm.

Sources:
https://www.c40.org/case_studies/the-worlds-largest-geothermal-heating-system-saves-up-to-4m-tons-co2-annually
https://www.verkis.com/projects/utilities/water-supply-systems/nr/982
https://nea.is/geothermal/direct-utilization/heat-pumps/
https://icelandmag.is/article/nine-fascinating-facts-about-geothermal-energy-and-reykjavik
https://askjaenergy.com/iceland-renewable-energy-sources/geothermal-different-utilization/
https://nautholsvik.is/en/
https://perlan.is/about-perlan/
https://www.epa.gov/coalash/coal-ash-basics

Research on Blue Lagoon and a skin condition: https://doi.org/10.1016/S0738-081X(96)00099-5

Filmed safely: https://www.tomscott.com/safe/

I'm at https://tomscott.com
on Twitter at https://twitter.com/tomscott
on Facebook at https://facebook.com/tomscott
and on Instagram as tomscottgo

Dr Alex George joins Lorraine to talk about the death of his 19 year old brother Ll≈∑r. Back in July Alex, announced that he had lost him to mental health and Ll≈∑r died just weeks before he was due to follow in his older brother's footsteps and start medical school. Alex recalls the moment he got that phone call and remembers Ll≈∑r's life. He encourages other to open up about their mental health and highlights the importance of making tangible change when it comes to mental health support.

snippet.title: Would You Swim In Power Plant Wastewater?
snippet.description:
Normally, the answer would be no. But in these very limited circumstances, at Iceland's Blue Lagoon, you can swim in geothermal power plant wastewater, and it's even healthy: although the marketing material doesn't usually mention it. Here's a story about geothermal energy, cheap heat, and how to keep some ducks warm.

Sources:
https://www.c40.org/case_studies/the-worlds-largest-geothermal-heating-system-saves-up-to-4m-tons-co2-annually
https://www.verkis.com/projects/utilities/water-supply-systems/nr/982
https://nea.is/geothermal/direct-utilization/heat-pumps/
https://icelandmag.is/article/nine-fascinating-facts-about-geothermal-energy-and-reykjavik
https://askjaenergy.com/iceland-renewable-energy-sources/geothermal-different-utilization/
https://nautholsvik.is/en/
https://perlan.is/about-perlan/
https://www.epa.gov/coalash/coal-ash-basics

Research on Blue Lagoon and a skin condition: https://doi.org/10.1016/S0738-081X(96)00099-5

Filmed safely: https://www.tomscott.com/safe/

I'm at https://tomscott.com
on Twitter at https://twitter.com/tomscott
on Facebook at https://facebook.com/tomscott
and on Instagram as tomscottgo

snippet.title: Star Wars: Squadrons ‚Äì ‚ÄúHunted‚Äù CG Short
snippet.description:
The New Republic fleet strikes the Imperial dockyard at Var-Shaa. Pre-order STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons now to get cosmetic items featured in this short film: https://www.ea.com/games/starwars/squadrons/cg-short-hunted 

The Empire‚Äôs retreat after a surprise attack marks yet another stumble in the wake of the second Death Star‚Äôs destruction. But for one member of Titan Squadron, the battle is far from over. Squadron Leader Varko Grey finds himself as the last TIE pilot on the battlefield, hunted relentlessly by a renegade New Republic X-wing in this standalone STAR WARS: Squadrons story.

Made in collaboration by Motive Studios, Lucasfilm, and ILM, "Hunted" is set before the events of STAR WARS: Squadrons, introducing you to one of the ace pilots who you'll be fighting alongside in the story to unfold.

Master the art of starfighter combat in the authentic piloting experience STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons, available October 2, 2020 on PlayStation¬Æ4, Xbox One, PC on EA.com, Steam, and Epic Games Store, and playable in Virtual Reality (VR) on PlayStation 4 and PC with cross-play support.

Pre-order to get the Var-Shaa Hunter and Var-Shaa Survivor cosmetic items, inspired by the short film: https://www.ea.com/games/starwars/squadrons/buy

Follow EA Star Wars:
https://twitter.com/EAStarWars
https://www.instagram.com/eastarwars/
https://www.facebook.com/EAStarWars/

About STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons:

ALL WINGS REPORT IN ‚Äì Plan skirmishes with your squadron in the briefing room before taking off to the evolving battlefields across the galaxy. Compete in intense 5v5 multiplayer dogfights or unite with your squadron to tip the scales in monumental fleet battles. Together, you‚Äôre the galaxy‚Äôs finest.

MASTER LEGENDARY STARFIGHTERS ‚Äì Take control of different classes of starfighters from both the New Republic and Imperial fleets ‚Äì including the agile A-wing and the devastating TIE bomber. Modify your ship, divert the power between its systems, and destroy your opponents in strategic space dogfights.

GET IN THE COCKPIT ‚Äì The cockpit is your home. Use its dashboards to your advantage and ‚Äì with just a thin hull of metal and glass between you and the perils of space ‚Äì feel the intensity of combat from a first-person perspective. Take off in thrilling multiplayer modes and a unique single-player STAR WARS‚Ñ¢ story, which covers a key campaign near the conclusion of the Galactic Civil War. Immerse yourself in the pilot‚Äôs seat completely with the option to play the entirety of STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons in Virtual Reality (VR) on PSVR and PC.

THE MISSION IS CLEAR ‚Äì STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons is a fully self-contained experience from day one, where you earn rewards through play. Climb the ranks and unlock new components like weapons, hulls, engines, shields, and cosmetic items in a clear path for progression that keeps gameplay fresh and engaging.

snippet.title: Did We Just Detect Life on Venus?
snippet.description:
The announcement of the detection of a possible biomarker in the atmosphere of Venus has shook up the field of astrobiology and grabbed headlines across the world. Today, we explore why Venus could plausibly host life, how this detection was made, and whether it really means that we've finally found extraterrestrial life. Written and presented by Prof Kipping, featuring guest Dr Caleb Scharf.

You can now support our research program and the Cool Worlds Lab at Columbia University: https://www.coolworldslab.com/support

Thank-you to Kevin Clark, Tom Widdowson, Denny Smith, Stephanie Hackley, Mark Sloan, Laura Sanborn, Kolos Kantor, Patrick Herman, Abel Aganbegyan, Claudio Bottaccini, Daniel Brunk, Douglas Daughaday, Scott Fincher, James Kindred, Andrew Jones, Jason Allen, Steven Baldwin, Jason Black, Stuart Brownlee, Shivam Chaturvedi, David Denholm, Tim Dorais, Glen Downton, Eneko Urrestarazu, Gordon Fulton, Sean Griffiths, Peter Halloran, John Jurcevic, Niklas Kildal, Jack Kobernick, Wes Kobernick, Valeri Kremer, Marc Lijoi, Sheri Loftin, Branden Loizides, Anatoliy Maslyanchuk, Blair Matson, Ocean Mcintyre, Laini Mitchell, Jeffrey Needle, Andr√© Pelletier, Juan Rivillas, Bret Robinson, Zenith Star, Lauren Steely, Ernest Stefan-Matyus, Mark Steven, Elena West, Barrett York, Tristan Zajonc, Preetumsingh Gowd, Shaun Kelsey, Chuck Wolfred, David Vennel, Emre Dessoi, Fahid Naeem, Francisco Rebolledo, Hauke Laging, James Falls, Jon Adams, Michael Gremillion, Pierce Rutherford, Trev Kline, Tristan Leger, Lasse Skov & Takashi Hanai.

::Paper announcing the detection::
‚ñ∫ Greaves, J. et al. (2020), "Phosphine gas in the cloud decks of Venus", Nature Astronomy: https://doi.org/10.1038/s41550-020-1174-4

::Other references used::
‚ñ∫ Sousa-Silva. C. et al. (2019), "Phosphine as a Biosignature Gas in Exoplanet Atmosphere", 
Astrobiology, 20, 235: https://arxiv.org/abs/1910.05224
‚ñ∫ Way, M. et al. (2016), "Was Venus the First Habitable World of our Solar System?", Geophysical Research Letters, 43, 8376: https://arxiv.org/abs/1608.00706
‚ñ∫ Moses, J. et al. (2005), "Photochemistry and diffusion in Jupiter's stratosphere: Constraints from ISO observations and comparisons with other giant planets", J. Geophys. Res., 110, E08001: https://doi.org/doi:10.1029/2005JE002411

::Movies/TV scenes used::
‚ñ∫ Roving Mars (2006) Buena Vista Pictures
‚ñ∫ Exploring Venus (2019) Magellan TV
‚ñ∫ Star Trek (1966) Paramount Pictures

::Other video footage used::
‚ñ∫ ALMA timelapse by ESO/Jos√© Francisco Salgado: https://youtu.be/Tn8Udphi6JA
‚ñ∫ Venus UV footage by Akatsuki/JAXA: https://www.isas.jaxa.jp/en/topics/002099.html
‚ñ∫ Bill Clinton footage form the Presidential Library & White House Television
‚ñ∫ Galaxies fly through by SDSS/Miguel Aragon/Mark Subbarao/Alex Szalay: https://youtu.be/08LBltePDZw

::Music::
Music used is licensed via Creative Commons (CC) Attribution License (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/)
‚ñ∫ "Fusion" by Indive licensed licensed under a CC Attribution license: https://indive.bandcamp.com
‚ñ∫ "Trace Correction" by Indive licensed licensed under a CC Attribution license: https://indive.bandcamp.com

snippet.title: LIVE: MPs debate UK Internal Market Bill in House of Commons 14 September 2020
snippet.description:
Debate on the UK Internal Market Bill begins from 2:15:55.

Watch the House of Commons from 2:30pm on Monday as three days of intensive debate and scrutiny on the United Kingdom Internal Market Bill begins.

Published last Wednesday, the Bill sets out rules for the operation of the UK internal market- trade between England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland- after the end of the transition period in January.

It proposes:
- The establishment of two legal principles, mutual recognition and non-discrimination, to ensure there are no new barriers for businesses trading across the UK, allowing a good or service to be sold anywhere in the UK without discrimination.
- Giving UK ministers powers to modify or ‚Äúdisapply‚Äù rules relating to the movement of goods from Northern Ireland to Great Britain that will come into force from 1 January, via the Northern Ireland Protocol, if both sides cannot agree beforehand.
- Powers to override previously agreed obligations with the EU in the Withdrawal Agreement on state aid - government support for businesses.

Want to find out more about what's happening in the House of Commons? Follow on Twitter at twitter.com/HouseofCommons
snippet.tags: ['PMQs', 'Boris Johnson', 'Keir Starmer']

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Fulham vs Arsenal (0-3) | Willian, Gabriel impress on debuts
snippet.description:
We got off to a flying start in the Premier League with a classy performance and three points at Craven Cottage.

Alex Lacazette, debutant Gabriel and Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang were on target while the outstanding Willian claimed two assists on his first appearance for us.

Fulham were bright in the opening moments and a misjudgement from Gabriel almost let in Aboubakar Kamara. Bernd Leno did well to claw the ball off his toes.

From then on, the home side could not live with our pace, movement and quality.

The first goal was a scrappy one. Mohamed Elneny found Aubameyang and his cutback was fired goalwards by Granit Xhaka. Tim Ream failed to clear, Willian reacted first to force a save from Marek Rodak and Lacazette tucked away the rebound.

Willian struck a free-kick against the base of a post with Rodak beaten, and Aubameyang almost scored from a trademark burst in behind the defence in the left-hand channel.

Gabriel grew in stature as the game unfolded and he marked his debut with a downward header to convert Willian's corner. That effectively put the match to bed very early in the second half.

After that it was a matter of how many we would score, and Aubameyang got the third and final goal thanks to a delightful crossfield pass from Willian and one of the captain's sumptuous finishes into the far corner.

There will be tougher tests ahead, but this was a hugely-encouraging start to the new campaign.

#arsenal #arsenalhighlights #willian #aubameyang #gabrielMagalhaes

ABOUT ARSENAL FC


Arsenal Football Club were formed in 1886. They have amassed 13 League titles, 14 FA Cups and many other major trophies since then. Their greatest players include: Thierry Henry, Dennis Bergkamp, Tony Adams, Ian Wright, Robert Pires, Liam Brady, Patrick Vieira, Cliff Bastin and Charlie George.

snippet.description:

snippet.title: Halal Food Recommended By Our Exes!
snippet.description:
In today's Food King Episode, our hosts go on a hunt to find the best halal dishes in Singapore! We've got halal ramen, Nasi Padang from Padang itself, and one of the best mee rebus we've ever tasted! This is halal food like we've never seen before!

1. Rumah Makan Minang 2:00
18 & 18A Kandahar Street, 198884
Opening hours: 8:30am - 7:30pm daily

Dishes:
- Ikan Bakar - $7.00
- Ayam Bakar Gulai - $3.50 ~ $4.00
- Sotong Masak Hitam - $7.00
- Lemak Pucuk Ubi - $4.50
- Ayam Belado Hijau - $3.50 ~ $4.50
- Beef Rendang - $4.00
- Ikan Asam Pedas 2pcs - $8.00
- Sayur Lemak Lodeh - $4.50
- Indonesian Tahu Telor - $7.00
- Teh Tarik ($1.30 Hot, $2 Cold)

2. Noosh Noodle Bar and Grill 7:21
8 Raffles Ave, #01-13B Esplanade Mall, Singapore 039802
Opening hours: 12 - 10pm daily

Dishes:
- Dome Filet Mignon Surf & Turf $38.90
- Smoked Duck Lemak Chilli Padi Spaghetti $18.90
- Niboshi Ramen with Sliced Beef $21.90
- Butterbeer $10.90 

3. Rahim Muslim Food 12:37
Blk 453A Ang Mo Kio Ave 10
Chong Boon Market, #01-01, Singapore 560453
Opening hours: 12:30 - 7pm, Mon - Sat

Dishes:
- Normal Mee Soto ($4.50)
- Power Mee Rebus ($4.50)

snippet.title: PM Lee Hsien Loong, Pritam Singh's exchange on 'free rider' voters
snippet.description:
Singapore PM Lee Hsien Loong and Leader of the Opposition Pritam Singh had an exchange in Parliament on Wednesday (Sep 2) on appeals to vote for the opposition. "If you say: 'Vote against the Government because somebody else will look after getting the PAP Government and you just become a free rider and you vote opposition - no harm, the PAP will still be there' - then I think the system must fail, because the system can only work if people vote sincerely," said Mr Lee.

"I don't think residents in Aljunied, Hougang for 30 years and even Sengkang as a result of the last election would appreciate being called 'free riders'," said Mr Singh. Read: https://cna.asia/3lGMIr8

snippet.title: Dune Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Beyond fear, destiny awaits. Watch the trailer for the highly anticipated #DuneMovie now. 


-----------------
https://www.facebook.com/dune
 https://twitter.com/dunemovie
https://www.instagram.com/dunemovie
-----------------

Oscar  nominee  Denis  Villeneuve  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049‚Äù)  directs  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary Pictures‚Äô ‚ÄúDune,‚Äù the big-screen adaptation of Frank Herbert‚Äôs seminal bestseller of the same name. A mythic and emotionally charged hero‚Äôs journey, ‚ÄúDune‚Äù tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet  in  the  universe  to  ensure  the  future  of  his  family  and  his  people.  As  malevolent  forces  explode  into conflict over the planet‚Äôs exclusive supply of the most precious resource in existence‚Äîa commodity capable of unlocking humanity‚Äôs greatest potential‚Äîonly those who can conquer their fear will survive.The film stars Oscar nominee Timoth√©e Chalamet (‚ÄúCall Me by Your Name,‚Äù  ‚ÄúLittle Women‚Äù), Rebecca Ferguson  (‚ÄúStephen  King‚Äôs  Doctor  Sleep,‚Äù   ‚ÄúMission:  Impossible  ‚Äì  Fallout‚Äù),  Oscar  Isaac  (the ‚ÄúStar  Wars‚Äù franchise) Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (‚ÄúMilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Infinity War‚Äù), Stellan Skarsg√•rd (HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúChernobyl,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Age of Ultron‚Äù), Dave Bautista (the ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù films, ‚ÄúAvengers: Endgame‚Äù), Stephen McKinley Henderson (‚ÄúFences,‚Äù ‚ÄúLady Bird‚Äù), Zendaya (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúEuphoria‚Äù), Chang Chen (‚ÄúMr.  Long,‚Äù ‚ÄúCrouching  Tiger,  Hidden  Dragon‚Äù),    David  Dastmalchian  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Dark  Knight‚Äù), Sharon  Duncan-Brewster  (‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story,‚Äù  Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúSex  Education‚Äù),   with  Oscar  nominee Charlotte Rampling (‚Äú45 Years,‚Äù ‚ÄúAssassin‚Äôs Creed‚Äù), with Jason Momoa (‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúGame of Thrones‚Äù), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men,‚Äù ‚ÄúSkyfall‚Äù).   Villeneuve directed ‚ÄúDune‚Äù from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts and Eric Roth based on the novel of the same name written by Frank Herbert.  Villeneuve also produced the film with Mary Parent, Cale Boyter  and  Joe  Caracciolo,  Jr.   The  executive  producers  are  Tanya  Lapointe,  Joshua  Grode,  Herbert  W.  Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt and Kim Herbert. Behind  the  scenes,  Villeneuve  reteamed  with  two-time  Oscar-nominated  production  designer  Patrice  Vermette  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúSicario,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Young  Victoria‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-nominated  editor  Joe  Walker  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚Äú12  Years  a  Slave‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-winning  visual  effects  supervisor  Paul  Lambert  (‚ÄúFirst Man,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù), and Oscar-winning special effects supervisor Gerd Nefzer (‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù).    He  also  collaborated  for  the  first  time  with  Oscar-nominated  director  of  photography  Greig  Fraser  (‚ÄúLion,‚Äù  ‚ÄúZero  Dark  Thirty,‚Äù  ‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story‚Äù);  three-time  Oscar-nominated  costume  designer  
Jacqueline West (‚ÄúThe Revenant,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Curious Case of Benjamin Button,‚Äù ‚ÄúQuills‚Äù) and co-costume designer Bob Morgan; and stunt coordinator Tom Struthers (‚ÄúThe Dark Knight‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúInception‚Äù).  Oscar-winning and multiple  Oscar-nominated  composer  Hans  Zimmer  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúInception,‚Äù  ‚ÄúGladiator,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Lion King‚Äù) is creating the score.  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary  Pictures  Present  ‚ÄúDune.‚Äù    The  film  is  slated  to  be  released  in  theaters on December 18, 2020.

Behind  the  scenes,  Villeneuve  reteamed  with  two-time  Oscar-nominated  production  designer  Patrice  Vermette  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúSicario,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Young  Victoria‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-nominated  editor  Joe  Walker  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚Äú12  Years  a  Slave‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-winning  visual  effects  supervisor  Paul  Lambert  (‚ÄúFirst Man,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù), and Oscar-winning special effects supervisor Gerd Nefzer (‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù).    He  also  collaborated  for  the  first  time  with  Oscar-nominated  director  of  photography  Greig  Fraser  (‚ÄúLion,‚Äù  ‚ÄúZero  Dark  Thirty,‚Äù  ‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story‚Äù);  three-time  Oscar-nominated  costume  designer  
Jacqueline West (‚ÄúThe Revenant,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Curious Case of Benjamin Button,‚Äù ‚ÄúQuills‚Äù) and co-costume designer Bob Morgan; and stunt coordinator Tom Struthers (‚ÄúThe Dark Knight‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúInception‚Äù).  Oscar-winning and multiple  Oscar-nominated  composer  Hans  Zimmer  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúInception,‚Äù  ‚ÄúGladiator,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Lion King‚Äù) is creating the score.  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary  Pictures  Present  ‚ÄúDune.‚Äù    The  film  is  slated  to  be  released  in  theaters on December 18, 2020.

snippet.title: Syekh Ali Jaber Ditusuk Orang Tak Dikenal Saat Mengisi Pengajian, Ini Penjelasan Polisi
snippet.description:
KOMPAS.TV - Ulama Syekh Ali Jaber ditusuk oleh orang tak dikenal di Masjid Afaludin Tamin Sukajawa, Tanjungkarang Barat, Bandar Lampung, Minggu (13/9/2020).

Saat itu Syekh Ali Jaber sedang mengisi sebuah tausyiah. Akibat kejadian itu, Syekh Ali Jaber mengalami luka tusukan di bagian bahu kanan.

"Saat ini (Syehk) sedang dirawat di Puskesmas Gedong Air," ucap Kapolsek Tanjungkarang Barat AKP David Jeckson Sianipar, dikutip dari Tribunjabar, Minggu.

David mengatakan, pihaknya juga sudah menangkap pelaku penusukan.

Adapun video penusukan Syekh Ali Jaber INI tersebar dan viral di media sosial. Dari video itu, tampak seorang pemuda berkaus biru masuk ke komplek masjid saat Syekh Ali Jaber sedang berbicang dengan dua jemaah di atas panggung.

Pemuda tersebut terlihat langsung berlari ke atas panggung dan menusukkan sebilah pisau ke arah perut sang ulama.

Syekh mencoba menghindar, tetapi bahu kanannya terluka.

Saat ini Syekh Ali Jaber sedang menjalani perawatan di puskesmas setempat.

Dust there's only dust
You're slipping to the dusk
There's nothing more
Besides your faults
That dig inside your soul

Pain there's no more pain
That fills your veins and tears
They broke your bones
They knocked you down
But there's still fire in your heart

Strive again
Defy the fate
Stand and fight
Beyond legends

Dry your tears
And don't look back
Rule the night
Beyond legends

That brings you to the dusk
Despite your fall could be this night
The legend will never fade

Fight your own fate
Be your legend
Burn bright like steel
You are legend

Strive again
Dry your tears
And don't look back
Rule the night
Beyond legends

Defy the fate
Stand and fight
Beyond legends

snippet.title: Christina Aguilera - Reflection (2020) (From "Mulan")
snippet.description:
Disney‚Äôs Mulan Now Streaming exclusively on Disney+ with Premier Access. Additional fee required. More info: http://disneyplus.com/mulan

‚ÄúReflection‚Äù
Performed by Christina Aguilera (@xtina) From Mulan (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack) Download/stream it here: https://disneymusic.co/Mulan?iqid=dmvevo ‚öî

Celebrate Mulan with new arrivals from shopDisney.com: http://bit.ly/shopDisneyMulan

‚öî ‚öî When the Emperor of China issues a decree that one man per family must serve in the Imperial Army to defend the country from Northern invaders, Hua Mulan, the eldest daughter of an honored warrior, steps in to take the place of her ailing father. Masquerading as a man, Hua Jun, she is tested every step of the way and must harness her inner-strength and embrace her true potential. It is an epic journey that will transform her into an honored warrior and earn her the respect of a grateful nation‚Ä¶and a proud father. ‚ÄúMulan‚Äù features a celebrated international cast that includes: Yifei Liu as Mulan; Donnie Yen as Commander Tung; Jason Scott Lee as B√∂ri Khan; Yoson An as Cheng Honghui; with Gong Li as Xianniang and Jet Li as the Emperor. The film is directed by Niki Caro from a screenplay by Rick Jaffa & Amanda Silver and Elizabeth Martin & Lauren Hynek based on the narrative poem ‚ÄúThe Ballad of Mulan.‚Äù

snippet.title: Dune Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Beyond fear, destiny awaits. Watch the trailer for the highly anticipated #DuneMovie now. 


-----------------
https://www.facebook.com/dune
 https://twitter.com/dunemovie
https://www.instagram.com/dunemovie
-----------------

Oscar  nominee  Denis  Villeneuve  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049‚Äù)  directs  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary Pictures‚Äô ‚ÄúDune,‚Äù the big-screen adaptation of Frank Herbert‚Äôs seminal bestseller of the same name. A mythic and emotionally charged hero‚Äôs journey, ‚ÄúDune‚Äù tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet  in  the  universe  to  ensure  the  future  of  his  family  and  his  people.  As  malevolent  forces  explode  into conflict over the planet‚Äôs exclusive supply of the most precious resource in existence‚Äîa commodity capable of unlocking humanity‚Äôs greatest potential‚Äîonly those who can conquer their fear will survive.The film stars Oscar nominee Timoth√©e Chalamet (‚ÄúCall Me by Your Name,‚Äù  ‚ÄúLittle Women‚Äù), Rebecca Ferguson  (‚ÄúStephen  King‚Äôs  Doctor  Sleep,‚Äù   ‚ÄúMission:  Impossible  ‚Äì  Fallout‚Äù),  Oscar  Isaac  (the ‚ÄúStar  Wars‚Äù franchise) Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (‚ÄúMilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Infinity War‚Äù), Stellan Skarsg√•rd (HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúChernobyl,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Age of Ultron‚Äù), Dave Bautista (the ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù films, ‚ÄúAvengers: Endgame‚Äù), Stephen McKinley Henderson (‚ÄúFences,‚Äù ‚ÄúLady Bird‚Äù), Zendaya (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúEuphoria‚Äù), Chang Chen (‚ÄúMr.  Long,‚Äù ‚ÄúCrouching  Tiger,  Hidden  Dragon‚Äù),    David  Dastmalchian  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Dark  Knight‚Äù), Sharon  Duncan-Brewster  (‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story,‚Äù  Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúSex  Education‚Äù),   with  Oscar  nominee Charlotte Rampling (‚Äú45 Years,‚Äù ‚ÄúAssassin‚Äôs Creed‚Äù), with Jason Momoa (‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúGame of Thrones‚Äù), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men,‚Äù ‚ÄúSkyfall‚Äù).   Villeneuve directed ‚ÄúDune‚Äù from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts and Eric Roth based on the novel of the same name written by Frank Herbert.  Villeneuve also produced the film with Mary Parent, Cale Boyter  and  Joe  Caracciolo,  Jr.   The  executive  producers  are  Tanya  Lapointe,  Joshua  Grode,  Herbert  W.  Gains, Jon Spaihts, Thomas Tull, Brian Herbert, Byron Merritt and Kim Herbert. Behind  the  scenes,  Villeneuve  reteamed  with  two-time  Oscar-nominated  production  designer  Patrice  Vermette  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúSicario,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Young  Victoria‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-nominated  editor  Joe  Walker  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚Äú12  Years  a  Slave‚Äù),  two-time  Oscar-winning  visual  effects  supervisor  Paul  Lambert  (‚ÄúFirst Man,‚Äù ‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù), and Oscar-winning special effects supervisor Gerd Nefzer (‚ÄúBlade Runner 2049‚Äù).    He  also  collaborated  for  the  first  time  with  Oscar-nominated  director  of  photography  Greig  Fraser  (‚ÄúLion,‚Äù  ‚ÄúZero  Dark  Thirty,‚Äù  ‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story‚Äù);  three-time  Oscar-nominated  costume  designer  
Jacqueline West (‚ÄúThe Revenant,‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Curious Case of Benjamin Button,‚Äù ‚ÄúQuills‚Äù) and co-costume designer Bob Morgan; and stunt coordinator Tom Struthers (‚ÄúThe Dark Knight‚Äù trilogy, ‚ÄúInception‚Äù).  Oscar-winning and multiple  Oscar-nominated  composer  Hans  Zimmer  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúInception,‚Äù  ‚ÄúGladiator,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Lion King‚Äù) is creating the score.  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary  Pictures  Present  ‚ÄúDune.‚Äù    The  film  is  slated  to  be  released  in  theaters on December 18, 2020.

Oscar  nominee  Denis  Villeneuve  (‚ÄúArrival,‚Äù  ‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049‚Äù)  directs  Warner  Bros.  Pictures  and  Legendary Pictures‚Äô ‚ÄúDune,‚Äù the big-screen adaptation of Frank Herbert‚Äôs seminal bestseller of the same name. A mythic and emotionally charged hero‚Äôs journey, ‚ÄúDune‚Äù tells the story of Paul Atreides, a brilliant and gifted young man born into a great destiny beyond his understanding, who must travel to the most dangerous planet  in  the  universe  to  ensure  the  future  of  his  family  and  his  people.  As  malevolent  forces  explode  into conflict over the planet‚Äôs exclusive supply of the most precious resource in existence‚Äîa commodity capable of unlocking humanity‚Äôs greatest potential‚Äîonly those who can conquer their fear will survive.The film stars Oscar nominee Timoth√©e Chalamet (‚ÄúCall Me by Your Name,‚Äù  ‚ÄúLittle Women‚Äù), Rebecca Ferguson  (‚ÄúStephen  King‚Äôs  Doctor  Sleep,‚Äù   ‚ÄúMission:  Impossible  ‚Äì  Fallout‚Äù),  Oscar  Isaac  (the ‚ÄúStar  Wars‚Äù franchise) Oscar nominee Josh Brolin (‚ÄúMilk,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Infinity War‚Äù), Stellan Skarsg√•rd (HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúChernobyl,‚Äù ‚ÄúAvengers: Age of Ultron‚Äù), Dave Bautista (the ‚ÄúGuardians of the Galaxy‚Äù films, ‚ÄúAvengers: Endgame‚Äù), Stephen McKinley Henderson (‚ÄúFences,‚Äù ‚ÄúLady Bird‚Äù), Zendaya (‚ÄúSpider-Man: Homecoming,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúEuphoria‚Äù), Chang Chen (‚ÄúMr.  Long,‚Äù ‚ÄúCrouching  Tiger,  Hidden  Dragon‚Äù),    David  Dastmalchian  (‚ÄúBlade  Runner  2049,‚Äù  ‚ÄúThe  Dark  Knight‚Äù), Sharon  Duncan-Brewster  (‚ÄúRogue  One:  A  Star  Wars  Story,‚Äù  Netflix‚Äôs ‚ÄúSex  Education‚Äù),   with  Oscar  nominee Charlotte Rampling (‚Äú45 Years,‚Äù ‚ÄúAssassin‚Äôs Creed‚Äù), with Jason Momoa (‚ÄúAquaman,‚Äù HBO‚Äôs ‚ÄúGame of Thrones‚Äù), and Oscar winner Javier Bardem (‚ÄúNo Country for Old Men,‚Äù ‚ÄúSkyfall‚Äù).   Villeneuve directed ‚ÄúDune‚Äù from a screenplay he co-wrote with Jon Spaihts and Eric Roth based on the novel of the same name written by Frank Herbert.  Villeneuve also produced the film with Mary Parent, Cale Boyter  and  Joe  Caracciolo,  Jr.   The  executive  producers  are  Tanya  Lapointe,  Joshua  Grode,  Herbert  W. snippet.title: Reporter investigates her own father's death in Australia's rural hospitals | 60 Minutes Australia
snippet.description:
Subscribe here: http://9Soci.al/chmP50wA97J Full Episodes: https://9now.app.link/uNP4qBkmN6 | The Greatest Loss (2020)

In a very special edition of 60 MINUTES, Liz Hayes reports on what is the most important, and personal, story of her career. However, it‚Äôs also a story that in modern Australia she shouldn‚Äôt need to tell. It‚Äôs about decent people in the country who are dying because of a rural health system that's broken and failing them. They are people like Liz‚Äôs precious dad. For many years Bryan Ryan was a farmer who lived near Taree, north of Newcastle in NSW. He was 88 years old when he died a year ago, but it‚Äôs highly likely he‚Äôd still be alive today if not for a catastrophic medical error that occurred while he was being treated in the rural health system.  As Liz reveals, what happened to her dad, Bryan Ryan, is inexcusable but it's just one of many cases that are as heart-breaking as they are tragic.

WATCH more of 60 Minutes Australia: https://www.60minutes.com.au 
LIKE 60 Minutes Australia on Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/60Minutes9

For forty years, 60 Minutes have been telling Australians the world‚Äôs greatest stories. Tales that changed history, our nation and our lives. Reporters Liz Hayes, Tom Steinfort, Tara Brown, Liam Bartlett and Sarah Abo look past the headlines because there is always a bigger picture. Sundays are for 60 Minutes.

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Fulham vs Arsenal (0-3) | Willian, Gabriel impress on debuts
snippet.description:
We got off to a flying start in the Premier League with a classy performance and three points at Craven Cottage.

Alex Lacazette, debutant Gabriel and Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang were on target while the outstanding Willian claimed two assists on his first appearance for us.

Fulham were bright in the opening moments and a misjudgement from Gabriel almost let in Aboubakar Kamara. Bernd Leno did well to claw the ball off his toes.

From then on, the home side could not live with our pace, movement and quality.

The first goal was a scrappy one. Mohamed Elneny found Aubameyang and his cutback was fired goalwards by Granit Xhaka. Tim Ream failed to clear, Willian reacted first to force a save from Marek Rodak and Lacazette tucked away the rebound.

Willian struck a free-kick against the base of a post with Rodak beaten, and Aubameyang almost scored from a trademark burst in behind the defence in the left-hand channel.

Gabriel grew in stature as the game unfolded and he marked his debut with a downward header to convert Willian's corner. That effectively put the match to bed very early in the second half.

After that it was a matter of how many we would score, and Aubameyang got the third and final goal thanks to a delightful crossfield pass from Willian and one of the captain's sumptuous finishes into the far corner.

There will be tougher tests ahead, but this was a hugely-encouraging start to the new campaign.

#arsenal #arsenalhighlights #willian #aubameyang #gabrielMagalhaes

snippet.title: I Tried Acrylic Pour Art For The First Time
snippet.description:
Hello friends! Apologies for the long absence, but we are trying to get things back on track. No, this video didn‚Äôt take us 3 months to make - we filmed a bunch of videos in July and this is the first of them to be released! It‚Äôs not a magnum opus, just supposed to be fun and lighthearted. If you want to read more about our plans, you can check out my blog post here:

https://www.safiyasnewintrosong.com/single-post/2020/09/04/where-have-we-been

Now, onto the video! A few weeks ago, somewhere deep in a visual ASMR YouTube rabbit hole, I discovered the online acrylic pour art community - where people essentially make interesting color combos of paint in a cup, then pour that cup onto a canvas or object - and then manipulate that object to create truly mesmerizing, rainbow, psychedelic pieces of art. And I was instantly hooked - just something about the way the paints flow from the cup and then slide around the canvas really got me, ya know? So I decided to pick an acrylic pour art video and try to follow it myself, to see if I could do it too. So I chose a "pouring guru", Tiktus color art, and got to work.

What do you guys think of my ~acrylic pouring adventure~?

This video is NOT sponsored!!

Safiya's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/safiyany/
Twitter: https://twitter.com/safiyajn
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/safnygaard/

The tutorial we followed is here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yndPwAMGEgg
You can check out Tiktus‚Äôs channel here: https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCeAvBShy5a2_vTFflQG_zWg

MUSIC
Via AudioNetwork

snippet.title: Why Parents Of 15-Year-Old Say They Fear He‚Äôs A Pedophile
snippet.description:
Kristin and Rick say they are concerned their 15-year-old son, Robbie, may be a pedophile. Kristin says her stepson admitted to her that he had strong sexual urges toward children over a year ago.

TELL DR. PHIL YOUR STORY: Chaos in your life?

‚ÄúHe said the only reason he hadn‚Äôt offended them was because they were going to tell,‚Äù says Kristin.

WATCH: Psychologist Says Early Developmental Trauma May Lead To Hypersexualized Behavior In Adolescents

Rick says, ‚ÄúIt was just such a shock that I didn‚Äôt know how to deal with it.‚Äù

The couple says they began supervising Robbie 24/7 and tried to find him a treatment facility placement. Then, says Kristin, Robbie threatened that if he didn‚Äôt get help that day ‚Äì he would rape one of his siblings, ‚ÄúSo we took him straight to the hospital.‚Äù

Kristin and Rick say Robbie has been in treatment for the past year and is due to come home soon, and they don‚Äôt know what to do. Can Dr. Phil help?

Check here to find out where you can watch more from Wednesday‚Äôs Dr. Phil.

TELL DR. PHIL YOUR STORY: Hopelessly in need of Dr. Phil's Help?

Dr. Phil uses the power of television to tell compelling stories about real people.

The Dr. Phil show provides the most comprehensive forum on mental health issues in the history of television. For over a decade, Dr. McGraw has used the show's platform to make psychology accessible and understandable to the general public by addressing important personal and social issues. Using his top-rated show as a teaching tool, he takes aim at the critical issues of our time, including the "silent epidemics" of bullying, drug abuse, domestic violence, depression, child abuse, suicide and various forms of severe mental illness.

snippet.title: Asphalt - Vom Steinbruch auf die Stra√üe | Die Nordreportage | NDR Doku
snippet.description:
#ndr #ndrdoku #asphalt
Ein hei√ües Pflaster f√ºr die Stra√üenarbeiter: Auf einer Kreuzung in Hannover muss 160 Grad hei√üer Asphalt verarbeitet werden. Das ist besonders anstrengend an warmen Sommertagen. snippet.title: Erz√§hlt Theo die Wahrheit √ºber den Brand?! üí•üò≤üî• | Berlin - Tag & Nacht #2278
snippet.description:
Theo ist so traurig und w√ºtend, dass sein eigener Sohn Jannes ihn nicht mehr sehen will, dass er sich total abschie√üt! Paula und Joe finden ihn vor und im Suff platzt es aus Theo heraus, was damals in Joes WG mit dem Brand, Peggy und der Explosion wirklich passiert ist... Oder haben sich Paula und Joe etwa verh√∂rt?! 

Die gescriptete Reality-Soap ‚ÄûBerlin - Tag & Nacht‚Äú zeigt die coolste WG Berlins, mit Themen wie  Freundschaft, Liebe,  Eifersucht, Aff√§ren, Gl√ºck, Freude und Leiden. Wie im echten Leben eben!
Alte wie neue WG-Bewohner, u. a. Ole, Joe, Peggy, Kr√§tze, Schmidti, Eule, Basti Paula, Piet, Milla, Leon und viele weitere, zeigen dir ihr Leben in Berlin, der bunten Metropole Deutschlands. Sie nehmen dich mit in ihre Wohngemeinschaften, auf ihre Arbeitspl√§tze, in den Club Matrix, den Friseursalon ‚ÄûSchnitte‚Äú sowie die Bar LA 14. Auch ein Tattoostudio und das Fitnessstudio Body Burn geh√∂ren zu den unterschiedlichen und wechselnden Handlungsorten der Serie. Die Gro√üstadt-Soap ‚ÄûBerlin ‚Äì Tag & Nacht‚Äú ist nicht zuletzt deshalb so beliebt, weil sie die Bewohner der WGs im Ringen mit allt√§glichen Problemen zeigt: Aff√§re und Eifersucht, Erfolgsdruck im Beruf sowie viele zwischenmenschliche Konflikte.

snippet.title: Star Wars: Squadrons ‚Äì ‚ÄúHunted‚Äù CG Short
snippet.description:
The New Republic fleet strikes the Imperial dockyard at Var-Shaa. Pre-order STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons now to get cosmetic items featured in this short film: https://www.ea.com/games/starwars/squadrons/cg-short-hunted 

The Empire‚Äôs retreat after a surprise attack marks yet another stumble in the wake of the second Death Star‚Äôs destruction. But for one member of Titan Squadron, the battle is far from over. Squadron Leader Varko Grey finds himself as the last TIE pilot on the battlefield, hunted relentlessly by a renegade New Republic X-wing in this standalone STAR WARS: Squadrons story.

Made in collaboration by Motive Studios, Lucasfilm, and ILM, "Hunted" is set before the events of STAR WARS: Squadrons, introducing you to one of the ace pilots who you'll be fighting alongside in the story to unfold.

Master the art of starfighter combat in the authentic piloting experience STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons, available October 2, 2020 on PlayStation¬Æ4, Xbox One, PC on EA.com, Steam, and Epic Games Store, and playable in Virtual Reality (VR) on PlayStation 4 and PC with cross-play support.

Pre-order to get the Var-Shaa Hunter and Var-Shaa Survivor cosmetic items, inspired by the short film: https://www.ea.com/games/starwars/squadrons/buy

Follow EA Star Wars:
https://twitter.com/EAStarWars
https://www.instagram.com/eastarwars/
https://www.facebook.com/EAStarWars/

About STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons:

ALL WINGS REPORT IN ‚Äì Plan skirmishes with your squadron in the briefing room before taking off to the evolving battlefields across the galaxy. Compete in intense 5v5 multiplayer dogfights or unite with your squadron to tip the scales in monumental fleet battles. Together, you‚Äôre the galaxy‚Äôs finest.

MASTER LEGENDARY STARFIGHTERS ‚Äì Take control of different classes of starfighters from both the New Republic and Imperial fleets ‚Äì including the agile A-wing and the devastating TIE bomber. Modify your ship, divert the power between its systems, and destroy your opponents in strategic space dogfights.

GET IN THE COCKPIT ‚Äì The cockpit is your home. Use its dashboards to your advantage and ‚Äì with just a thin hull of metal and glass between you and the perils of space ‚Äì feel the intensity of combat from a first-person perspective. Take off in thrilling multiplayer modes and a unique single-player STAR WARS‚Ñ¢ story, which covers a key campaign near the conclusion of the Galactic Civil War. Immerse yourself in the pilot‚Äôs seat completely with the option to play the entirety of STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons in Virtual Reality (VR) on PSVR and PC.

THE MISSION IS CLEAR ‚Äì STAR WARS‚Ñ¢: Squadrons is a fully self-contained experience from day one, where you earn rewards through play. Climb the ranks and unlock new components like weapons, hulls, engines, shields, and cosmetic items in a clear path for progression that keeps gameplay fresh and engaging.
